# remove currency sign from column('price ' and 'EMI')
cars_data['price']=cars_data['prices'].replace('[\₹]','',regex=True)
In [23]:
# remove sign from EMI column
cars_data['EMI']=cars_data['EMI'].replace('[\₹]','',regex=True)
In [24]:
cars_data.drop('prices',axis=1,inplace=True)
In [ ]:
In [25]:
# remove comma from price column and EMI column 
cars_data['price']=cars_data['price'].replace(',','',regex=True)
cars_data['EMI']=cars_data['EMI'].replace(',','',regex=True)
In [26]:
# REPLACE text into numbers for better understanding
x={'1ST OWNER':'1','2ND OWNER':'2','3RD OWNER':'3'}

# create a new column named( no of columns)
cars_data['no. of owner']=cars_data['owners'].replace(x,regex=True)
In [27]:
# drop owners column
cars_data.drop('owners',axis=1,inplace=True)
In [28]:
# remove 'KM' from driven_km 
cars_data['driven km']=cars_data['driven km'].replace('KM','',regex=True)
In [29]:
cars_data['driven km']=cars_data['driven km'].replace(',','',regex=True)
In [30]:
# convert object to int
cars_data['driven km']=cars_data['driven km'].astype(int)

cars_data['EMI']=cars_data['EMI'].astype(int)

cars_data['no. of owner']=cars_data['no. of owner'].astype(int)
In [32]:
cars_data['price']=cars_data['price'].astype(float)
In [37]:
# convert ibject into float 
divisor=1000
cars_data['price']=cars_data['price']/divisor

Defining the accuracy function
In [95]:
def accuracy(y_pred,y_test):
    from sklearn import metrics
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    import numpy as np
    import pandas as pd
    print("MAE",metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_test,y_pred))
    print("RMSE",np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred)))    # using heatmap to plot accuracy
    plt.scatter(y_test,y_pred)
    plt.xlabel('predicted values')
    plt.ylabel('true values')
    plt.show()
